PREP: CLEAN: Wash hands. Remove and discard skin from chicken. CLEAN: Wash hands. In 3 1/2- to 4-quart crockery cooker, combine all ingredients except chicken; mix well. Place chicken on top of mixture. COOK: Cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours or until squash is done and internal juices of chicken run clear and chicken is very tender. (Insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 180 degrees F.) With forks, remove chicken from bones, then cut chicken into pieces. Stir into vegetable mixture. SERVE: Serve in shallow soup bowls with hot bread and crisp tossed salad, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.